path.id: In 1907, the most important European powers are divided into two major alliances. On the Balkan, Serbia, Austria Greece and the Ottoman empire gamble for influence.

On June 28th, Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria is assassinated in Serbia while visiting Sarajevo. Austria accuses Serbian officials of being involed in the incident, aiming to annex Serbia.
